Vodacom is increasing prices on certain plans from 1 April 2018, the company announced. Vodacom said the price increases are due to “the government regulatory Value Added Tax increase” and its “annual price adjustment”. “In our ongoing commitment to lower the cost of communication, many bundles have not increased in price,” said Vodacom. The terms and conditions of the packages remain unchanged, it added. The prepaid and contract price changes are detailed in the tables below. Vodacom said users can check what price plan they are on using the following methods.                         